title: Pennsylvania Firm Recalls Pork Products Imported Without Benefit of Inspection
summary: WASHINGTON, JANUARY 21, 2015 House of Bricks Realty, Inc., a Wilkes-Barre, PA establishment, is recalling approximately 130 pounds of French pork rillette because they were not presented at the U.S. point of entry for inspection, the U.S. Department of Agricultures Food Safety and Inspection Service...
